product_name: Bronze Plaque - Dark Brown - Lugs with Studs
ml_tags: In Loving Memory Of RON JARICK 4 April 1941 - 22 June 2021 Though your smile is gone, your hand we cannot touch, You left us peaceful memories, of the one we loved so much. Hard working hands at rest, your heart was in the land, You gave your all to those around you, when love was in demand. Having you in our lives, we’ve all been greatly blessed, But now the time has arrived, for you to be at rest. Your memory now our keepsake, which we’ll never part, God has you in his keeping, we have you in our heart. MUCHED LOVED FATHER IN LAW TO MICHAEL AND MARIA ADORED GRANDFATHER OF CAITLIN AND THOMAS LOVING HUSBAND OF ANN, CHERISHED FARTHER OF ROGER AND TRINA
